<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_fyddæragæn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fyddæragæn</orth><form type="variant"><orth>fyddæradæn</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fuddæragæn</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>назло</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>to spite</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>ænæcæstwarzon adæm xattæj-xatt fyddæragæn mītæ dær kænync</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>недоброжелательные люди иногда действуют назло</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>unfriendly people sometimes act out of spite</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1934 II 8</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>fons fuddæragæn fæccaǧtoncæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>назло истребили скот</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>cattle were exterminated out of spite</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>176%l4%l</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>kustmæ fuddæradæn næ cæwuncæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>назло не идут на работу</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>(they) don't go to work out of spite</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>285%l4%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>ænæcæstwarzon adæm xattæj-xatt fyddæragæn mītæ dær kænync</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>недоброжелательные люди иногда действуют назло</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>unfriendly people sometimes act out of spite</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1934 II 8</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>fons fuddæragæn fæccaǧtoncæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>назло истребили скот</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>cattle were exterminated out of spite</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>176%l4%l</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>kustmæ fuddæradæn næ cæwuncæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>назло не идут на работу</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>(they) don't go to work out of spite</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>285%l4%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Форма дательного падежа (на %i-æn%i) от %i*fyddærag%i или %i*fyddærad%i, разлагающихся на <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fyddær"/> ‘хуже’ и суффикс %i-ag%i или %i-ad%i. Оба варианта обоснованы: в первом случае мы можем видеть суффикс %i-ag%i, означающий ‘предназначенность для чего-либо’, во втором — абстрактный суффикс %i-ad%i. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fydænæn"/>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Dative (%i-æn%i) form of %i*fyddærag%i or %i*fyddærad%i, which can be decomposed into <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fyddær"/> ‘worse’ and suffix %i-ag%i or %i-ad%i. Both options are justified: in the first case, we can see the suffix %i-ag%i, meaning ‘predestination for something’, in the second case there is the abstract suffix %i-ad%i. Compare with <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fydænæn"/>.</etym></entry>